Normalize path

Installation

install.packages("imager")
library(imager)

Preprocess the data

Coordinates:

CImg uses standard image coordinates: the origin is at the top left corner, with the x axis pointing right and the y axis pointing down. imager uses the same coordinate system, except the origin is now (1,1) and not (0,0) (the reason being that R indices start at 1 and not at 0). The number of pixels along the x axis is called the width, along the y axis its height, along the z axis its depth and finally the number of colour channels is called spectrum.
